From 5a1160c52642ccb9f5a0c1fd62f5ee69f20ed2ba Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vijayan Balasubramanian <balasvij@amazon.com>
Date: Sat, 21 Mar 2026 11:37:59 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 23/53] Add FaissScorableByteVectorValues with external
 iterator support for scoring (#3192)

The FAISS-backed ByteVectorValues is a random-access store that cannot
produce a DocIndexIterator on its own, which is required by VectorScorer
to drive scoring. Introduce FaissScorableByteVectorValues to wrap raw
byte vectors with scoring capability via FlatVectorsScorer, and update
VectorSearcher.getByteVectorValues to accept a DocIndexIterator that
the scorer uses for document traversal.

Signed-off-by: Vijayan Balasubramanian <balasvij@amazon.com>
